Opposites attract! Jennifer Hudson wows in daring mesh mini as she joins preppy fiance David Otunga at Clive Davis' pre-Grammy bash
By

Karen Mizoguchi for MailOnline

Published:
  01:49 EDT, 8 February 2015

 | 
Updated:
  11:16 EDT, 8 February 2015














e-mail








26
shares

 
          57
View  comments



They have been engaged for more than seven years.And on Saturday Jennifer Hudson shows that opposites do indeed attract as she joined fiance David Otunga at the Clive Davis pre-Grammy soiree in Los Angeles.The 33-year-old multi-award winning performer turned heads on the red carpet as she showed her unique sense of style in a black mesh mini dress with thigh high boots. Scroll down for video   





 Hot mama! Jennifer Hudson attended the Clive Davis pre-Grammy party in Los Angeles on Saturday  





 Date night: The 33-year-old Grammy winner was accompanied by fiance David Otunga who proudly wrapped his arm around his belovedHer longtime love, 34, proudly wrapped his arm around her, while displaying his own fashion sense in a preppy sweater and tie.His wife-to-be made a seductive statement revealing her black bra in the long sleeve see-through frock.If the short frock wasn't enough, Jennifer oozed major sex appeal with fishnet stockings and thigh high patent leather black boots.She wore a purple lip for an added cherry on top of her stunning outfit.






  





 Sexy statement: The Academy Award winning actress turned heads on the red carpet wearing a black mesh mini dress  





 For David's eyes only: The mother-of-one reveaked her black bra in the long sleeve see-through frock  





 LBD: Jennifer oozed major sex appeal with fishnet stockings and thigh high patent leather black bootsWhile David was more conservatively dressed, it was clear the pair remain devoted.Harvard Law School graduate David - who was a former WWE champion wrestler - covered up his muscular build in a black and white plaid dress shirt, grey sweater, black tie and grey trousers.It was a fun date night for the engaged couple, who will surely be attending the Grammy Awards as Jennifer is nominated for Best R&B Performance for her single It's Your World featuring R Kelly.  





 Dynamic duo: Jennifer and Iggy Azalea performed their duet Trouble at the soiree






Since becoming a breakout star from the third season of American Idol in 2006, Jennifer has gone on to win an Oscar, Grammy, SAG and Golden Globe Award.'You know what you don't have to win,' she said to Wall Street Journal about her seventh place finish on the FOX singing competition.Adding: 'When I did it I took it as an experience I always called it the boot camp of the industry it preps you and teaches you what its about. 'You don't always have to win as long as I have my talent you know that's all I need and I have to keep singing and keep going for it and that's what I did. It's a matter of what you do with the opportunity. I started singing at the age of seven and I always knew what I wanted to do.'  





 Her start: Jennifer became a breakout star after appearing on the third season of American Idol in 2006  





 Private plane: 'Me n my hudsonettes r on our way back to la ! Team Jhud ! Let's roll'And on her success in the entertainment business, she revealed she wants to continue her passions both in music and acting.'I hope I never have to choose between the two. Now I'm doing Empire so that's a bit of singing and acting. That's going great. But I do want to continue acting and singing I just hope I don't have to choose,' she said.It was recently announced that Jennifer will be making her Broadway debut in the revival of The Color Purple.  





 More projects on the horizon: Fans will be able to catch Jennifer on the hit FOX show Empire as well as her Broadway debut in The Color Purple



